%% Fig 4.14 — Sequence: student dashboard composition (the "wow endpoint") (P4)
%% Source: author, derived from students/StudentController + StudentDashboardService (ARCHITECTURE.md §8)
sequenceDiagram
    actor S as Student
    participant FE as Next.js (web)
    participant SC as StudentController
    participant DS as StudentDashboardService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    S->>FE: open growth dashboard
    FE->>SC: GET /api/students/{id}/dashboard
    SC->>DS: getDashboard(id)
    Note over DS,DB: @Transactional(readOnly = true)
    DS->>DB: read student_metrics (composite + 6 norms)
    DS->>DB: read metric_snapshots (trend, by date)
    DS->>DB: read recent grades / attendance / behaviour
    DS->>DS: build radar (6 dimensions), growth areas, risk flag
    DS-->>SC: DashboardDto {composite, radar, trend, risk, recent}
    SC-->>FE: 200 ApiResponse (single composed payload)
